The #mobile #banking app has become the virtual bank. I feel more secure when I'm talking to my mobile banking app than when I'm talking to Alexa or if I'm going through FB Messenger." - @ehigdon #AIBanking18"
Your #mobile #banking application is the perfect place to roll out #chatbot functionality as the first channel." - @ehigdon #AIBanking18"

“Why would you not want to go and engage your #mobile #banking audience with this type of functionality. It creates a much richer opportunity to help drive deeper adoption of those features and functions. - @ehigdon @JavelinStrategy #AIBanking18"

What’s your question behind that question? The conversation needs to go beyond ‘what’s my balance’. Otherwise, your #chatbot interactions may end up being much more of a monologue, than the proactive financial conversation that you are imaging at the start. @ehigdon #AIBanking18

“As you outline the functionality you want to enable with your #chatbot consider how you already meet the needs of customers through #digital deliveries to ensure that your chatbot will deliver clear value over and above what's already available.” @ehigdon #AIBanking18
Absolutely! Customers want instant gratification.
It’s not only about providing context to the customer about “how much did I spend?” It’s asking for those little bits of additional #data form that customer. @ehigdon #AIBanking18

“I’m not going to come back to that #chatbot if I don’t know what that chatbot can do better for me that I don’t already get through my app alone, through my text alerts or through whatever channel I rely on today.” - @ehigdon #AIBanking18
It's important to add actionable context along with that response from the #chatbot . It needs to be proactive and anticipate what may be next for the consumer. @ehigdon #AIBanking18 #AI

“What can this #chatbot do for me? That’s the number one question that most customers ask. The answer needs to be very clear. If that answer is not clear then the value is not clear.” - @ehigdon @JavelinStrategy #AIBanking18

Many consumers today see #chatbot 's as more of a novelty than something that can really provide real value to them. How do we break through that? What can we do to make chatbot functionality stand out from other #digital deliveries?" - @ehigdon @JavelinStrategy #AIBanking18"

I have a fundamental problem with building a skill" for Alexa. I shouldn't have to remember how to invoke my USAA account. If I say, "Alexa, did I pay my credit card bill this month?" It should know what I'm asking and not have to explain I want to engage the USAA skill."

Completely agree! As the vendor that designed the AI brain behind @USAAs Alexa Skill, we're focused on improving #CX through real conversations around banking, not just simple voice commands. Bringing those conversations to a mobile app integrates voice for users who are still...
...new to the technology, while early voice adopters are more comfortable going straight to a voice device.

There are real opportunities to make financial management feel more like a conversation, rather than a chore. Some unique ways to do that is to create experiences that build trust." - @apknole @VentureBeat"
Merely tying a specific voice command to an existing on-screen activity isn’t #voicefirst . I’m sorry!

We've worked with banks that integrate voice into their native mobile banking app. This provides a nice, seamless experience. In terms of clunky-ness, that will occur any time the AI has hard-coded intents as rules. Not only does that make the AI brittle, it's also not scalable!
